WEBVTT

00:01.744 --> 00:02.835
<i> - A woman cooks.</i>

00:02.986 --> 00:05.487
<i> - You look tired,</i> beti.
- I am tired.

00:05.564 --> 00:07.064
I just need to get through
the next two days,

00:07.082 --> 00:08.415
take the bar,
and then I can rest.

00:08.567 --> 00:11.010
<i> - Shouldn't you be studying</i>
<i> instead of cooking?</i>

00:11.161 --> 00:12.919
- I am mentally reviewing
tort law while I grate.

00:13.072 --> 00:14.755
<i> - Hmm.</i>
- Well, this has been fun,

00:14.831 --> 00:16.331
as usual, but I have to go.

00:16.333 --> 00:18.166
I have to finish making
my chunda.

00:18.244 --> 00:19.518
And next time you make it,
Mom, add a pinch of turmeric.

00:19.745 --> 00:23.171
<i> - Wait, before you rush off,</i>
<i> I found someone for you.</i>

00:23.190 --> 00:25.265
<i> - Angali Auntie's</i>
<i> nephew's son.</i>

00:25.342 --> 00:27.359
<i> He's a doctor.</i>
- Mom, I can't see that.

00:27.436 --> 00:28.952
Can you hold it a little back?

00:28.954 --> 00:32.531
<i> - I emailed it to you.</i>
<i> - Good family. Good career.</i>

00:32.608 --> 00:35.868
<i> His mother's a bit of a cow,</i>
<i> but his father is very kind.</i>

00:35.870 --> 00:37.261
- He's handsome.

00:37.263 --> 00:38.686
<i> - Is it too fast,</i> deekra?

00:38.764 --> 00:40.280
<i> We can wait a little bit</i>
<i> if you want.</i>

00:40.432 --> 00:42.282
<i> - She's already 26.</i>
<i> You want her to get stuck</i>

00:42.359 --> 00:44.025
<i> with someone divorced</i>
<i> or unemployed?</i>

00:44.103 --> 00:46.211
<i> Uh-uh.</i>
<i> She needs a good husband.</i>

00:46.288 --> 00:49.214
- He's perfect on paper.
<i> - What do you think?</i>

00:49.366 --> 00:50.883
<i> I need to get back</i>
<i> to his mother.</i>

00:51.034 --> 00:52.551
[door thuds closed]

00:52.702 --> 00:55.554
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

00:55.631 --> 01:00.784
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:00.786 --> 01:02.469
- Just tell them no.

01:02.546 --> 01:04.379
- I told you,
I want it to be arranged.

01:04.398 --> 01:06.456
I said that to you
on our first date.

01:06.458 --> 01:08.216
- Yeah, like four years ago.

01:08.235 --> 01:12.053
Before all the birthdays,
the friends, the fights.

01:12.073 --> 01:15.890
One pregnancy scare,
two trips to the ER.

01:15.968 --> 01:18.819
Nish, that was before
we fell in love.

01:18.895 --> 01:20.913
- I know.

01:21.064 --> 01:23.415
- Do you still love me?
- So much.

01:23.567 --> 01:24.583
- Then how are you okay

01:24.734 --> 01:26.418
with the idea
of marrying someone else?

01:26.570 --> 01:29.237
- I know it's difficult
to understand,

01:29.256 --> 01:32.165
but I want my kids to grow up
eating the same foods I ate

01:32.318 --> 01:35.669
and speaking the language
and knowing their culture.

01:35.763 --> 01:38.246
- I can't change the fact
that I'm not Indian.

01:38.307 --> 01:42.250
- No. I don't want you to.
You're perfect the way you are.

01:42.328 --> 01:44.177
It's just that
law school's ending,

01:44.330 --> 01:47.922
and I need to--
I need to start figuring out

01:48.000 --> 01:49.775
what I'm doing
with this phase of my life.

01:49.926 --> 01:53.278
- Well, if you're ready
to get married...

01:53.430 --> 01:54.838
marry me.

01:54.857 --> 01:57.616
- [laughs]

01:57.767 --> 01:59.601
You don't believe in marriage.

01:59.620 --> 02:01.936
<i> [gentle music]</i>

02:01.956 --> 02:04.531
What are you doing?

02:04.683 --> 02:07.459
Oh, my God.

02:07.611 --> 02:10.111
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:10.131 --> 02:12.280
- I didn't believe in marriage.

02:12.299 --> 02:16.360
And then I met
the most complicated,

02:16.378 --> 02:20.547
challenging, hilarious,
beautiful woman in the world.

02:20.699 --> 02:24.034
And then I did believe.

02:24.052 --> 02:26.536
Will you marry me, Nish?

02:26.555 --> 02:30.798
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

02:30.876 --> 02:35.320
<i> [dreamy music]</i>

02:35.397 --> 02:42.327
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:45.833 --> 02:49.409
<i> [tropical music]</i>

02:49.561 --> 02:56.216
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:01.831 --> 03:03.831
- Good morning, Javier.

03:03.851 --> 03:06.351
- Ruby, Elena.
- Hey.

03:06.428 --> 03:08.020
- Late again.
- Was not.

03:08.096 --> 03:09.913
- Well, you were almost late.

03:09.932 --> 03:12.916
- You can't be almost late.
Either you are or you aren't.

03:12.935 --> 03:14.434
- Listen, I'm very busy.

03:14.511 --> 03:17.345
I don't have time for all of
the sexual tension between us.

03:17.364 --> 03:18.588
- Okay--

03:18.607 --> 03:20.199
- Nisha Shah.
- [ahem]

03:20.350 --> 03:22.350
- This is Elena Roarke,
your host.

03:22.428 --> 03:23.927
- And this is my associate,
Ruby.

03:23.946 --> 03:25.929
It's so nice to meet you,
Ms. Shah.

03:25.948 --> 03:26.854
- So wonderful
to meet both of you.

03:26.932 --> 03:28.207
I can't wait to begin.

03:28.358 --> 03:30.542
- Well then, let's go
to my office and get started.

03:30.619 --> 03:32.336
After you.

03:36.884 --> 03:38.775
- Whoa, whoa. Hold up. Elena.

03:38.777 --> 03:40.219
- Yes.

03:40.295 --> 03:42.462
- I'm gonna stop
by your office later.

03:42.614 --> 03:44.130
I have a question.

03:44.283 --> 03:46.783
- Can you ask me now?
- Eh, it's about a fantasy.

03:46.785 --> 03:49.302
I have one.
- What? Um...mm-mm.

03:49.396 --> 03:51.713
- Don't you even want
to know what it is?

03:51.732 --> 03:53.065
- Nope.

03:58.964 --> 04:00.313
- Which one should I marry?

04:00.390 --> 04:02.966
- Yeah, the Island
doesn't answer questions.

04:02.985 --> 04:04.484
It fulfills fantasies.

04:04.636 --> 04:06.152
- Okay.

04:06.247 --> 04:08.488
My fantasy is for an answer.

04:08.565 --> 04:09.973
[laughter]

04:09.992 --> 04:11.899
- Your semantics won't get you
as far here

04:11.977 --> 04:13.752
as they do in the courtroom.

04:13.903 --> 04:15.254
- Look.

04:15.330 --> 04:18.740
- Oh. Wow. This is, um...

04:18.817 --> 04:20.908
laminated.
- Wow, okay.

04:20.928 --> 04:23.077
- I've hit every life goal
either on time

04:23.155 --> 04:25.155
or ahead of time,
and marriage is next.

04:25.157 --> 04:27.824
- Oh, yes. "To do:
Say, 'I do.'"

04:27.826 --> 04:32.271
- I normally know what I want.
But this time, I'm at a loss.

04:32.498 --> 04:35.065
- So tell us a little bit
about each man.

04:36.351 --> 04:37.317
- Hmm.

04:40.188 --> 04:45.191
Well, Josh is creative
and thoughtful and smart.

04:45.344 --> 04:47.861
And he doesn't make much,
but he's developing an app.

04:47.937 --> 04:49.346
And, well, I can't say much
about it,

04:49.348 --> 04:51.531
but it has tremendous
potential.

04:51.608 --> 04:52.866
And I can be a little intense.

04:52.942 --> 04:56.128
- Is that right?
- Josh evens me out.

04:56.279 --> 04:58.463
He makes me feel like
everything's gonna be okay.

04:58.615 --> 04:59.798
- But Savin, see, now,

04:59.875 --> 05:02.042
I can see myself
building a life with him.

05:02.118 --> 05:04.027
He's stable. He's ambitious.

05:04.046 --> 05:05.378
And he understands
where I come from.

05:05.455 --> 05:06.621
I mean, we're gonna connect

05:06.698 --> 05:08.974
in a way that Josh
and I never could.

05:09.051 --> 05:11.310
These need a pinch of cinnamon.

05:12.704 --> 05:13.979
- Oh. It says here that Savin

05:14.056 --> 05:16.706
is a head
of cardiology at City Memorial.

05:16.725 --> 05:18.892
- And he's not even 30.

05:19.044 --> 05:22.379
I mean,
he is the responsible choice.

05:22.381 --> 05:25.991
A pinch of cinnamon and two
more minutes in the oven.

05:26.026 --> 05:28.552
- Thanks.
So what do you think, Ruby?

05:28.570 --> 05:30.570
The creative
and full of potential,

05:30.647 --> 05:32.389
or the safe and stable?

05:32.407 --> 05:34.391
- Well,
I-I really couldn't say.

05:34.393 --> 05:38.244
- Look, if I don't get married,
it means no kids by 30,

05:38.397 --> 05:41.656
empty nest by 52,
and retirement by 55.

05:41.675 --> 05:43.157
And if I don't retire by 55,

05:43.159 --> 05:46.086
I won't have time
to pursue my actual dream:

05:46.162 --> 05:48.680
opening a restaurant by 60.

05:48.757 --> 05:50.256
- Wow.

05:50.409 --> 05:52.909
- I'm 26 and out of time.

05:52.928 --> 05:56.096
- So let's try this again.

05:56.248 --> 05:58.190
What can the Island do for you?

05:58.266 --> 06:01.193
- Marriage changes people.
I know that.

06:01.269 --> 06:05.271
My fantasy is to find out

06:05.424 --> 06:07.941
which version
of who I become is better.

06:08.017 --> 06:10.276
- You see, that we can do.
- Really?

06:10.429 --> 06:14.164
- Welcome to Fantasy Island.

06:16.435 --> 06:18.268
- You probably think
it's old fashioned

06:18.270 --> 06:20.270
to care
so much about getting married.

06:20.272 --> 06:22.547
- No, I understand.

06:22.699 --> 06:24.941
I was married for decades.

06:24.960 --> 06:27.444
- You were what?
- [light laugh]

06:27.446 --> 06:29.036
You know
one thing I learned?

06:29.056 --> 06:31.948
It's not just about
who you marry.

06:31.950 --> 06:34.709
It's about the commitment
you make

06:34.728 --> 06:36.970
and the life you build

06:37.122 --> 06:40.232
and the love, that...
well, grows over time.

06:41.068 --> 06:43.793
Oh, and okay. And here we are.

06:43.812 --> 06:45.462
Good luck. Okay?

06:45.480 --> 06:46.813
- Okay.

06:46.965 --> 06:50.300
- Prepare for the unexpected.

06:50.302 --> 06:53.470
<i> [mysterious music]</i>

06:53.488 --> 06:57.064
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:57.084 --> 07:00.401
<i> [traditional music]</i>

07:00.479 --> 07:04.423
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:04.574 --> 07:06.073
- We're married.

07:06.151 --> 07:10.670
- I wonder how long it will
take before they feel normal.

07:10.822 --> 07:13.673
- You're expected inside
in ten minutes.

07:13.825 --> 07:15.659
Sumit Uncle is already drunk.

07:15.661 --> 07:17.269
And Priya Mahee is mad

07:17.420 --> 07:18.920
she isn't sitting
closer to the stage.

07:18.997 --> 07:20.230
- We'll be right in.

07:26.613 --> 07:28.447
- So this is nice.

07:29.691 --> 07:31.357
Kind of weird.
[both chuckle]

07:31.434 --> 07:33.100
- I have something for you.

07:33.120 --> 07:35.603
I know we kept
the whole thing traditional,

07:35.622 --> 07:37.622
but I wrote vows for you.

07:37.699 --> 07:39.516
May I?

07:39.534 --> 07:42.461
Nisha, I am probably gonna
make a thousand mistakes

07:42.612 --> 07:44.278
getting to know you,

07:44.298 --> 07:48.133
but I already know
your smile makes me smile...

07:48.284 --> 07:51.285
and that our conversations
will never be boring.

07:51.363 --> 07:54.714
I promise to support you
however you need me to.

07:54.866 --> 07:57.142
I promise to be a good father.

07:57.293 --> 07:58.718
I promise to treat your family
with respect

07:58.795 --> 08:00.294
and to tell your mother

08:00.314 --> 08:04.191
her dhokra is the...[kiss]
best I've ever had.

08:05.819 --> 08:08.378
Oh, I promise to tell my mom
to shut up

08:08.380 --> 08:10.396
when she starts
to nag you about

08:10.398 --> 08:13.474
what detergent you're using
or the length of your hair.

08:13.494 --> 08:17.737
I promise to make our family
the center of my life

08:17.889 --> 08:20.481
for better and for worse.

08:20.501 --> 08:22.209
Was that okay?

08:24.563 --> 08:26.246
- Tch, tch, tch, tch.
- Sorry, Mom.

08:26.398 --> 08:28.898
- Don't be sorry.
I want grandchildren.

08:28.917 --> 08:29.991
Just don't make them
in the middle

08:30.068 --> 08:31.659
of the hallway of the hotel,
okay?

08:31.678 --> 08:33.236
- Okay.
Have I ever mentioned

08:33.255 --> 08:36.740
that your<i> dhokra</i> is the best
I've ever eaten?

08:37.500 --> 08:40.076
- You have ten minutes
before you're expected inside.

08:40.095 --> 08:41.520
Sumit Uncle is already drunk

08:41.671 --> 08:43.747
and Priya Masi is mad that
there's meat in the buffet.

08:43.749 --> 08:45.065
Come.
- Thanks, Mom.

08:51.089 --> 08:52.531
- How do you want to spend
the first ten minutes

08:52.607 --> 08:54.090
as man and wife?

08:54.109 --> 08:57.369
- It'll take me 20
just to get out of this thing.

08:57.445 --> 09:00.446
- Here.

09:00.599 --> 09:02.356
This is for you.

09:02.376 --> 09:03.649
- Thanks?

09:03.727 --> 09:05.377
- I know you were saving
that money for a house,

09:05.528 --> 09:06.711
and giving it to me
for the startup

09:06.863 --> 09:08.213
was not part of the plan,

09:08.290 --> 09:10.382
but I still wanted us
to have a place that's ours.

09:10.533 --> 09:13.459
It's small, but...it's got
a lot of character.

09:13.536 --> 09:15.295
- You signed a lease
without even talking to me?

09:15.447 --> 09:17.264
- I thought
it would be romantic.

09:19.059 --> 09:21.284
But roses are romantic.

09:21.303 --> 09:24.804
A lease is a big decision
that I made unilaterally.

09:24.881 --> 09:26.064
[sighs]

09:26.141 --> 09:27.732
- We'll stick to the plan?

09:27.884 --> 09:31.052
- Yes. I will move into
your apartment,

09:31.129 --> 09:33.129
and we'll make it ours.

09:33.148 --> 09:36.557
And I will gracefully
back out of this lease.

09:36.635 --> 09:39.393
- Well, you are married
to a lawyer.

09:39.471 --> 09:40.820
I got your back.

09:40.897 --> 09:42.305
Hey, I think we just had

09:42.307 --> 09:43.973
our first fight
as a married couple.

09:43.992 --> 09:45.308
- Oh, seems like a fitting way

09:45.310 --> 09:48.645
to spend the first
ten minutes as man and wife.

09:48.663 --> 09:50.255
- Ready?

09:50.332 --> 09:51.906
[speaking Gujarati]

09:51.983 --> 09:53.333
- Yes. He knows, Mom.

09:53.485 --> 09:56.336
- Josh, you have to touch
the elder's feet as you--

09:56.488 --> 09:57.821
- He knows, Mom.

09:57.839 --> 09:59.264
- Excuse me
for wanting to make sure

09:59.415 --> 10:02.249
this non-Indian boy
doesn't embarrass the family.

10:02.269 --> 10:04.019
Come.

10:06.297 --> 10:08.422
- Okay, when you said
this would take 20 minutes,

10:08.500 --> 10:10.257
I assumed you were joking.
- [giggles]

10:10.319 --> 10:14.029
- Can I just unravel you
like a roll of toilet paper?

10:18.844 --> 10:20.619
- Okay.
- Oh. Right.

10:20.695 --> 10:23.955
Kinda wanted
to get down on the cardboard.

10:24.032 --> 10:25.773
- Go wait in the other room.

10:25.851 --> 10:28.109
I have a surprise.
- Ooh.

10:28.128 --> 10:30.370
Can I watch "Chopped"
while I wait?

10:30.522 --> 10:32.613
- [laughing] Go.

10:32.633 --> 10:35.449
<i> [mellow music]</i>

10:35.527 --> 10:40.713
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:40.790 --> 10:43.716
<i> [mysterious music]</i>

10:43.718 --> 10:50.982
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:54.655 --> 10:56.713
[breath hitches]

10:56.731 --> 10:58.381
Maybe I shouldn't have.

10:58.400 --> 11:00.717
- No, it's fine.
I wasn't expecting you to--

11:00.719 --> 11:03.052
- It's--it's too much.

11:03.071 --> 11:04.645
I'll just go wear PJs.

11:04.665 --> 11:05.997
- Wait. You look beautiful.

11:06.074 --> 11:09.392
<i> [uplifting music]</i>

11:09.411 --> 11:13.746
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:13.899 --> 11:16.708
<i> [electronic music]</i>

11:16.860 --> 11:24.057
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:31.583 --> 11:33.750
- I just want to remember
this moment,

11:33.752 --> 11:35.418
how you look right now.

11:35.420 --> 11:39.531
- You're such a cheeseball.
- You love this cheeseball.

11:39.607 --> 11:46.496
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:12.474 --> 12:14.232
- How is it going?

12:16.962 --> 12:18.361
<i> [wind rushing]</i>

12:22.133 --> 12:25.059
- Okay. That was intense.

12:25.136 --> 12:26.302
- You know, a mild fantasy

12:26.321 --> 12:29.063
wouldn't be much
to write home about, would it?

12:29.082 --> 12:30.731
- Savin and Josh
are both great.

12:30.751 --> 12:33.918
- A good man is hard to find.
And you found two.

12:34.070 --> 12:35.903
I'm waiting to pop
the champagne.

12:35.905 --> 12:37.922
[laughing] Come on.

12:37.999 --> 12:39.758
- This isn't helping me
know who to choose.

12:39.909 --> 12:42.743
- You likely need more than
a glimpse of your wedding night

12:42.763 --> 12:44.262
to choose a life partner.

12:44.413 --> 12:47.098
Okay, what's next on
your life goals list?

12:47.175 --> 12:49.100
- First kid by 28.
- You're right.

12:49.252 --> 12:51.019
How could I forget?
[chuckles]

12:54.332 --> 12:57.500
Um, you should head outside,
you know, get some fresh air.

12:57.519 --> 12:59.360
Yeah, go, go, go.

13:02.007 --> 13:04.857
- [retching]

13:05.010 --> 13:06.451
- [exhales]

13:06.678 --> 13:08.620
- Why doesn't anyone tell you
morning sickness lasts all day?

13:08.696 --> 13:11.180
- Because everyone
except for us is terrible.

13:11.182 --> 13:12.365
[toilet flushing]

13:12.441 --> 13:15.201
It's gonna be okay, all right?

13:15.278 --> 13:20.948
Look, when the baby does come,
I'll get a real job.

13:20.967 --> 13:22.542
- You already gave up
Silicon Valley

13:22.618 --> 13:25.711
so I can stay closer
to my family.

13:25.788 --> 13:27.030
I'll go back to work

13:27.032 --> 13:29.382
and my parents can help
with the baby.

13:29.458 --> 13:31.200
- You want to go back to work?

13:31.219 --> 13:33.553
- I wanna have electricity
and hot water.

13:33.629 --> 13:36.797
- [chuckles]

13:36.891 --> 13:39.559
When my app
makes $100 million,

13:39.711 --> 13:41.878
you can quit.

13:41.896 --> 13:43.822
We'll have nannies
for the kids.

13:43.898 --> 13:46.825
You can open up
that restaurant.

13:46.976 --> 13:49.310
What's gonna be on the menu?

13:49.329 --> 13:51.054
- Hmm.

13:51.056 --> 13:53.056
Peri peri chicken,

13:53.074 --> 13:56.000
steak--but only ever served
rare, as God intended.

13:56.152 --> 13:58.319
- Of course. What else?

13:58.338 --> 14:00.246
- Cream...

14:00.398 --> 14:01.840
Oh, no.

14:01.991 --> 14:04.092
Talking about food
was a mistake.

14:05.995 --> 14:08.162
No. I'm okay.

14:08.239 --> 14:09.755
We're doing
everything you said.

14:09.908 --> 14:11.090
I wear red every Friday,

14:11.242 --> 14:12.216
and we're fasting
three days a week.

14:12.293 --> 14:14.501
- She drinks tulsi water
every morning.

14:14.579 --> 14:16.503
- Still no baby?

14:16.581 --> 14:17.856
- No.

14:18.007 --> 14:20.191
- You were a good match
when you got married.

14:20.268 --> 14:24.511
But now, the spirits
aren't in your favor.

14:24.531 --> 14:26.030
It's not meant to be.

14:26.107 --> 14:28.091
- There has to be something
we can do.

14:28.093 --> 14:30.109
Anything.
- Can you give us a minute?

14:30.261 --> 14:32.287
- I'll wait in the kitchen.
- Yeah.

14:34.374 --> 14:35.781
- I can do this.

14:35.934 --> 14:37.934
- But do we really want to?

14:37.952 --> 14:40.861
The IVF alone was brutal,
and now this...

14:40.881 --> 14:43.006
- What are you suggesting?

14:44.033 --> 14:45.791
- We've been at it
for two years.

14:45.886 --> 14:48.887
Maybe it's time we just start
considering other options.

14:48.963 --> 14:50.704
Adoption or a donor.

14:50.782 --> 14:52.465
Or...

14:52.541 --> 14:55.376
maybe we just don't have kids
at all and we travel more.

14:55.395 --> 14:56.728
- No.

14:56.955 --> 14:59.355
Kids was always
part of the plan.

15:00.792 --> 15:03.234
- Plans can change.

15:03.386 --> 15:05.719
- That's not who I am, Sav.

15:05.797 --> 15:08.990
<i> [sorrowful music]</i>

15:13.896 --> 15:16.080
It's Josh.

15:16.232 --> 15:18.082
He's the one
I'm supposed to be with.

15:18.309 --> 15:22.736
- Are you sure about that?
- I want to have a child.

15:22.814 --> 15:24.088
And Savin can't give me that.

15:24.240 --> 15:26.090
- Okay, what about
the rest of your list?

15:26.242 --> 15:28.317
Don't you want to see
how it all pans out?

15:28.319 --> 15:30.911
- Part of me just wants to make
a decision and be done with it.

15:30.931 --> 15:33.673
- Your fantasy is to figure out
the best version of yourself,

15:33.825 --> 15:37.418
and I don't know that
you've done that yet, right?

15:37.437 --> 15:40.329
Go have some dinner and relax.

15:40.348 --> 15:44.016
Let the future unfold, hmm?

15:44.093 --> 15:47.594
<i> [traditional music]</i>

15:47.689 --> 15:50.673
<i> [lively music]</i>

15:50.675 --> 15:57.580
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:25.301 --> 16:26.192
[groans]

16:31.491 --> 16:34.175
[line ringing]

16:34.252 --> 16:37.996
Hey. Hey, it's me.
Um...

16:38.147 --> 16:40.498
I need your help.
[chuckles]

16:40.649 --> 16:43.209
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:46.748 --> 16:49.173
- Hi. Yes, I ordered the steak,

16:49.325 --> 16:52.159
but you cooked it one minute
too long for a medium-rare.

16:52.178 --> 16:56.180
And I'd recommend fewer capers
in the butter sauce.

16:56.332 --> 16:58.182
I'm actually
about to take a bath,

16:58.259 --> 17:00.426
so if it could come
in about 40 minutes,

17:00.578 --> 17:01.744
that would be great.

17:01.763 --> 17:03.913
Thank you.

17:03.931 --> 17:06.858
<i> [relaxing R&B music]</i>

17:06.934 --> 17:09.510
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:09.529 --> 17:11.195
<i> [wind rushing]</i>

17:11.347 --> 17:14.282
[cell phone rings]

17:16.928 --> 17:19.779
<i> [tense music]</i>

17:19.931 --> 17:27.086
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:28.106 --> 17:30.965
Hi, Mom.
<i> - [speaking Gujarati]</i>

17:32.777 --> 17:34.260
- Why?

17:42.562 --> 17:46.305
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:46.457 --> 17:49.141
- We're on our way, Mrs. Shah.

17:49.294 --> 17:51.051
- This can't be happening.
This can't be happening.

17:51.071 --> 17:52.737
- Hey, hey, hey, right now,
we just need to focus

17:52.888 --> 17:54.146
on getting there, okay?
I got you.

17:54.299 --> 17:55.573
<i> - Nisha?</i>
- It's okay, buddy.

17:55.724 --> 17:56.649
- Mommy's okay.

17:56.801 --> 17:59.135
<i> - Nisha!</i>
- [panting]

17:59.137 --> 18:01.120
<i> - Nisha?</i>

18:01.806 --> 18:04.731
- [gasps]

18:04.751 --> 18:07.585
<i> [tense music]</i>

18:07.662 --> 18:09.995
[sobbing]

18:10.072 --> 18:12.665
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.

18:12.741 --> 18:14.258
It's all right.

18:14.410 --> 18:18.221
It's just a fantasy.
You're gonna be okay.

18:25.012 --> 18:26.270
- Come on. Come on.

18:26.422 --> 18:28.147
Come on, come on, come on.

18:32.946 --> 18:35.279
Yeah, we're stuck.

18:35.431 --> 18:37.006
- Well, it's okay.
Just--you know what?

18:37.008 --> 18:38.858
Just drive me home, and I'll--

18:39.010 --> 18:39.933
I'll deal with my car
in the morning.

18:39.953 --> 18:42.178
It's fine.
- No. No, no.

18:42.196 --> 18:44.622
<i> We're</i> stuck.
Both of us.

18:44.699 --> 18:46.958
- What are you doing?
- We're gonna make camp.

18:47.185 --> 18:49.201
A nice, flat spot
right over that way.

18:49.278 --> 18:50.277
- What?

18:50.463 --> 18:52.521
What, we're gonna
spend the night out here?

18:52.540 --> 18:54.206
Are you crazy?

18:54.283 --> 18:56.116
- It's too dark
to hike back now.

18:56.194 --> 18:57.802
Might as well try
to get comfortable.

18:57.995 --> 19:00.638
Here you go.
Go ahead, take this.

19:00.715 --> 19:02.640
<i> [gentle music]</i>

19:02.717 --> 19:04.809
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:04.886 --> 19:07.395
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

19:09.390 --> 19:11.390
- I didn't ask to see this.

19:11.484 --> 19:14.635
I wanted to know about
Josh and Savin, not about this.

19:14.654 --> 19:16.045
- Well,

19:16.063 --> 19:19.991
hard times tell you
who people really are.

19:20.735 --> 19:23.736
After my dad died,

19:23.812 --> 19:27.665
Mel would get me an éclair
every year on his birthday

19:27.742 --> 19:29.834
to celebrate him.

19:30.061 --> 19:32.745
And I hate éclairs.
[laughs]

19:32.897 --> 19:36.248
But my dad loved them.

19:36.401 --> 19:39.902
And it was actually lovely

19:39.904 --> 19:45.074
to have someone there
who knew and...

19:45.076 --> 19:47.426
cared enough to do that for me.

19:47.503 --> 19:51.689
You can't hide from
the hard parts of life.

19:51.766 --> 19:53.749
All you can do

19:53.768 --> 19:58.345
is find the people who will
support you through them.

19:58.439 --> 20:01.106
<i> [soft music]</i>

20:01.183 --> 20:03.492
- [sniffles]

20:05.020 --> 20:08.447
I have to face this, don't I?

20:08.599 --> 20:10.933
- Mm-hmm.

20:10.952 --> 20:14.361
<i> [music swells]</i>

20:14.439 --> 20:16.547
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:16.624 --> 20:19.550
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

20:19.627 --> 20:21.444
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:21.462 --> 20:24.037
Well, you ready?

20:24.115 --> 20:25.798
- Ready.
- Okay.

20:25.950 --> 20:29.060
You know, I think
you're meant to do this.

20:30.955 --> 20:33.397
- I'm scared.

20:33.624 --> 20:35.641
- Hey, look.

20:36.569 --> 20:39.795
Just be a tiny bit more brave
than you are scared,

20:39.797 --> 20:43.557
and you'll be okay. Okay?

20:43.576 --> 20:44.891
All right.

20:44.911 --> 20:52.208
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:07.341 --> 21:10.751
- He was really lucky
to have you.

21:10.770 --> 21:15.422
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:15.500 --> 21:17.942
- I think it's time
we move Mom in with us.

21:18.093 --> 21:21.003
- Maybe we should
talk about this later.

21:21.005 --> 21:22.280
- She can't manage on her own.

21:22.431 --> 21:25.432
- Nish, we can move her
into a home nearby,

21:25.510 --> 21:27.702
but she can't live with us.

21:29.289 --> 21:32.290
- We don't move our parents
into homes.

21:32.366 --> 21:35.626
- But your mom hates me.
- She hates everybody.

21:35.703 --> 21:40.423
- [sobbing softly]

21:49.642 --> 21:52.292
- I must go greet the family.

21:52.386 --> 21:55.888
- It's time for her
to come stay with us.

21:55.964 --> 21:59.150
I can clear out my office.

21:59.301 --> 22:00.559
- Okay.

22:00.636 --> 22:02.636
I think we should
look into adoption.

22:02.713 --> 22:04.655
- Really?

22:04.732 --> 22:06.157
- This is the reminder I needed

22:06.308 --> 22:11.311
that...life is short
and unexpected.

22:11.331 --> 22:13.998
And sometimes
we need to pivot.

22:15.001 --> 22:17.484
- That's all it is.
A pivot.

22:17.562 --> 22:21.047
- And there's no one I would
rather do it with than you.

22:27.088 --> 22:29.755
- Ahh...there we go.

22:29.907 --> 22:31.349
- I'm impressed.

22:31.576 --> 22:34.743
- I'm very impressive.
- Okay. Relax.

22:34.762 --> 22:38.505
And in the morning,
we should hike to my house.

22:38.524 --> 22:39.932
- [laughing] What?

22:40.084 --> 22:42.193
Well, well,
I finally get to see

22:42.269 --> 22:43.861
the famous
Roarke family hacienda.

22:43.938 --> 22:46.364
- You've never been?
- I've never been invited.

22:46.440 --> 22:52.111
- Hmm. Well, it's much closer
than the resort from here.

22:52.187 --> 22:54.246
- Then that's what we'll do.

22:56.934 --> 22:58.292
Salud.

23:01.622 --> 23:04.548
<i> [acoustic music]</i>

23:04.625 --> 23:07.610
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:07.703 --> 23:09.945
- Salud, Javier.
- [laughs]

23:09.964 --> 23:15.784
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:15.786 --> 23:18.562
<i> [tropical music]</i>

23:18.639 --> 23:22.900
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:22.977 --> 23:25.294
- They're six and five,

23:25.296 --> 23:26.979
but they think
they're teenagers already.

23:27.073 --> 23:28.964
- I know what you mean, man.

23:29.057 --> 23:30.741
My kids are better at
technology at three and seven

23:30.893 --> 23:32.301
than I ever will be.

23:32.303 --> 23:33.727
- They're smart
when they aren't trying to

23:33.746 --> 23:36.247
kill each other.
[all chuckling]

23:36.398 --> 23:37.640
- Nisha?

23:37.642 --> 23:41.293
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:45.908 --> 23:48.317
<i> [suave music]</i>

23:48.319 --> 23:50.094
- I heard you were
in San Francisco.

23:50.245 --> 23:52.263
Well, less heard,
more read on "Forbes."

23:52.490 --> 23:54.323
- Yeah, I moved out
right after graduation.

23:54.416 --> 23:56.583
Needed a change
of scenery after...

23:56.936 --> 23:59.011
Anyway, I got hooked up with
a couple of the right people.

23:59.163 --> 24:00.938
One thing led to another,
and the rest is history.

24:01.015 --> 24:04.333
It was 2% a good idea,
98% luck.

24:04.351 --> 24:07.093
- The most humble
billionaire I know.

24:07.113 --> 24:09.405
- Nisha, how have you been?

24:10.766 --> 24:12.766
- Not reading enough "Forbes,"
apparently.

24:12.785 --> 24:14.267
- You're still
at the same law firm?

24:14.345 --> 24:16.603
- No, I actually stopped
practicing a few years ago.

24:16.622 --> 24:18.104
- Well, that's amazing.

24:18.124 --> 24:19.457
You finally opened up
that restaurant.

24:19.533 --> 24:21.125
I knew you would take
the leap one day.

24:21.276 --> 24:22.943
I'm so proud of you.
- Restaurant?

24:22.962 --> 24:24.962
Um, no, no, actually,
I stopped working,

24:25.039 --> 24:27.022
you know, after we had kids.

24:27.041 --> 24:28.114
It just didn't make sense
for both of us

24:28.192 --> 24:29.783
to be so busy all the time.

24:29.860 --> 24:31.284
Savin was so busy

24:31.304 --> 24:33.696
with the hospital
and his private practice, so...

24:33.698 --> 24:36.215
it just made the most sense
for our family.

24:36.309 --> 24:39.051
- Well, that's great.
I'm sure you're a great mom.

24:39.203 --> 24:41.294
[small laugh]
Can I get my former roommate

24:41.314 --> 24:42.387
another drink?

24:42.556 --> 24:45.131
- A prince among men.
- I'll go with you.

24:45.209 --> 24:47.026
I want to see
what wines they have.

24:53.159 --> 24:54.825
- You look really great,
by the way.

24:55.052 --> 24:57.036
- So do you.

24:59.499 --> 25:05.318
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:05.338 --> 25:08.063
- Why would you embarrass me
like that?

25:08.065 --> 25:09.990
- That was not my intention.

25:10.067 --> 25:11.342
- You called my app
a "little hobby."

25:11.569 --> 25:15.087
- It was just a slip.
I've had too much wine.

25:15.239 --> 25:18.423
- I knew you resented me
for not making as much as you.

25:18.576 --> 25:22.502
- It's not about the money.
I carry us financially.

25:22.522 --> 25:25.264
And on top of that, you have
to make me the buzzkill?

25:25.416 --> 25:28.083
You get to be the fun parent,
and I have to be the one

25:28.102 --> 25:29.268
to tell you you can't pull him
out of school

25:29.420 --> 25:32.512
on a random Tuesday
to take him to the zoo?

25:32.532 --> 25:33.531
Two waters, please.

25:33.682 --> 25:35.199
- Whiskey, neat, double.

25:35.276 --> 25:40.612
- What's going on?
- We're going under.

25:40.765 --> 25:41.764
- We're having a fight.
We're--

25:41.782 --> 25:44.208
- Not us.

25:44.359 --> 25:46.210
The app.

25:47.529 --> 25:49.863
My "hobby" is dead.

25:49.940 --> 25:52.758
I didn't know how to tell you.

25:55.963 --> 25:58.705
- You used to
tell me everything.

25:58.724 --> 26:01.133
- Don't put this all on me.

26:01.209 --> 26:03.561
We haven't been like
that in a long time.

26:10.903 --> 26:14.554
- [chuckling]

26:14.632 --> 26:17.466
Oh, I love this song.

26:17.468 --> 26:18.984
- You two should go dance.
I'll watch your drinks.

26:19.061 --> 26:21.394
- I don't dance, unfortunately.

26:21.414 --> 26:23.080
- I knew you couldn't
really be the whole package.

26:23.157 --> 26:25.006
[both laugh]

26:25.008 --> 26:26.584
- Well, you two go.

26:26.660 --> 26:28.586
She's always looking
for a dance partner.

26:28.662 --> 26:30.996
- Oh, no, he doesn't want
to be saddled with me.

26:31.148 --> 26:33.073
- It would be my pleasure.

26:33.092 --> 26:35.484
<i> - ♪ If your color's gone</i>
<i> won't let me ♪</i>

26:35.486 --> 26:39.504
<i> ♪ And it's pulling me down</i>
<i> down down down ♪</i>

26:39.581 --> 26:43.175
<i> ♪ You and me,</i>
<i> we can be magic, magic ♪</i>

26:43.327 --> 26:46.419
<i> ♪ Come on and see,</i>
<i> we can be magic, magic ♪</i>

26:46.497 --> 26:50.182
<i> ♪ Do you believe in magic</i>
<i> magic ♪</i>

26:50.334 --> 26:53.093
<i> ♪ Come on and see we can</i>
<i> be magic, magic ♪</i>

26:53.112 --> 26:55.946
<i> ♪ Falling falling fast ♪</i>

26:56.023 --> 26:59.191
<i> ♪ Burning, burning, burning</i>
<i> bright ♪</i>

26:59.267 --> 27:02.511
<i> ♪ Like stars across the sky ♪</i>

27:02.529 --> 27:06.123
<i> ♪ Like stars</i>
<i> across the sky ♪</i>

27:06.274 --> 27:09.034
<i> ♪ Even in the dark ♪</i>

27:09.186 --> 27:12.445
<i> ♪ We can light, light up</i>
<i> the night ♪</i>

27:12.523 --> 27:14.873
<i> ♪ Like stars</i>
<i> across the sky... ♪</i>

27:14.950 --> 27:18.694
[laughter]

27:18.712 --> 27:21.363
- [laughing] Stop!

27:21.365 --> 27:24.058
[laughter]

27:32.467 --> 27:34.193
[exhales]

27:37.231 --> 27:39.657
[chuckles]
My eyes are up here.

27:39.884 --> 27:43.643
- Um, where did you
get that scar?

27:43.737 --> 27:45.237
- Ah...
- Okay.

27:45.313 --> 27:47.814
You don't have to talk
about it if it's too personal.

27:47.833 --> 27:49.649
It's okay.

27:49.669 --> 27:52.485
- Oh, it's okay.

27:52.505 --> 27:55.898
Before I came to the Island,
I was in the Air Force.

27:55.916 --> 27:58.008
Lost some friends
in unthinkable ways.

27:59.904 --> 28:01.720
I got injured.

28:03.349 --> 28:04.497
And when I was sent home,

28:04.591 --> 28:07.000
I thought the worst
of it was over, but...

28:07.077 --> 28:09.594
just couldn't adjust.

28:09.671 --> 28:11.188
Never thought I'd feel
comfortable anyplace

28:11.306 --> 28:14.274
ever again,
then I found the Island.

28:17.029 --> 28:20.272
- I'm glad the Island
can give that to you.

28:20.348 --> 28:23.442
- It's not the same for you,
is it?

28:23.536 --> 28:24.760
- I'm comfortable here.

28:24.762 --> 28:26.278
- Yeah, but it's not
what you would choose.

28:26.430 --> 28:28.354
- I did choose to be here.

28:28.374 --> 28:32.358
And what we do...
is very important.

28:32.378 --> 28:34.861
- But...

28:34.939 --> 28:37.122
- I'm a little drunk,

28:37.274 --> 28:40.551
so I'm just gonna...
[clicks tongue] go to bed.

28:40.702 --> 28:43.036
- Oh, okay. Oh, you don't want
to tell me your secrets?

28:43.055 --> 28:44.463
- No, I don't.
- So hold on, hold on.

28:44.615 --> 28:47.466
- No, I don't. I don't.
- Let me give it a shot.

28:47.618 --> 28:48.559
- Oh.
- Yeah.

28:48.635 --> 28:50.118
- Interesting.
- Yeah, are you ready?

28:50.137 --> 28:51.620
- Ready.
- Here we go.

28:51.622 --> 28:52.879
- Vamos.

28:52.957 --> 28:54.047
- When you're stressed,

28:54.066 --> 28:56.066
you wear your hair
in a ponytail.

28:56.143 --> 28:58.293
And I try not to bother you
on those days.

28:58.295 --> 29:01.146
Your favorite treat
is chocolate cake,

29:01.298 --> 29:03.741
which you eat with your hands.

29:03.892 --> 29:05.467
And when you're drunk,

29:05.469 --> 29:09.913
your cheeks get all red
and you look sunburned.

29:10.065 --> 29:13.492
You act so tough,
but deep down, you're a softie.

29:13.644 --> 29:17.070
And the thing that you hate
more than anything

29:17.089 --> 29:19.465
is asking people for help.

29:20.667 --> 29:22.667
- That was thorough.
- Hmm!

29:22.820 --> 29:24.669
I pay attention.

29:24.746 --> 29:26.246
- Yeah.

29:26.340 --> 29:27.672
- You know, people from
all over the world come here

29:27.749 --> 29:29.491
asking you for help.

29:29.510 --> 29:32.186
Why is it so hard
for you to do the same?

29:33.680 --> 29:34.938
- People make promises.

29:35.015 --> 29:38.016
I-I've made promises, Javier.

29:38.168 --> 29:41.186
Big promises, and...

29:41.263 --> 29:43.405
I've broken them.

29:45.359 --> 29:46.950
- You know, I would've
done anything

29:47.027 --> 29:49.769
for the guys in my unit--
anything.

29:50.122 --> 29:53.106
As far as I'm concerned,
you're my unit now.

29:53.183 --> 29:57.019
If you ever need anything,
I'll be there.

29:57.021 --> 29:58.945
No questions asked.

29:58.964 --> 30:01.840
<i> [gentle music]</i>

30:01.992 --> 30:09.264
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:10.976 --> 30:13.227
- Let's go to--
let's go to sleep.

30:23.656 --> 30:25.730
- Good night, Elena.

30:25.883 --> 30:27.807
- Good night, Javier.

30:27.827 --> 30:31.644
[chill electronic pop music]

30:31.664 --> 30:34.498
[singer vocalizing softly]

30:34.575 --> 30:41.547
♪ ♪

30:43.901 --> 30:46.751
- It was really nice to see
you again, Nish.

30:46.904 --> 30:50.222
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:58.858 --> 31:01.525
- Thanks for keeping
my drink warm.

31:03.028 --> 31:05.604
- Are you still
in love with him?

31:05.698 --> 31:08.490
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:12.763 --> 31:15.855
<i> [Latin guitar music]</i>

31:15.933 --> 31:18.600
- Just up ahead.

31:18.602 --> 31:21.620
- Are you sure this
is the right way?

31:21.696 --> 31:24.548
- Hey, trust me. Okay?

31:28.703 --> 31:31.630
- Wait, was this your fantasy?

31:31.706 --> 31:34.057
- Come on, Roarke.
Just figuring that out?

31:34.134 --> 31:36.709
- Oh, so you wanted me
to want you.

31:36.787 --> 31:38.228
- Wait, what?

31:38.380 --> 31:40.789
No, I wanted
to spend time with you.

31:40.882 --> 31:43.975
Get to know you, talk.
I swear.

31:44.128 --> 31:47.220
- Well, that's--
it's almost sweet.

31:47.297 --> 31:49.389
- It's nice to know
you want me.

31:49.408 --> 31:50.390
- I didn't say that.
- No, I heard you.

31:50.467 --> 31:51.483
- No, I didn't.
- You said it.

31:51.559 --> 31:52.817
- No, I didn't.
- You said--you said--

31:52.912 --> 31:55.228
- I didn't say that--
- "You wanted me to want you,"

31:55.305 --> 31:57.489
which means you want me.

31:57.641 --> 31:59.399
- You're annoying.

31:59.493 --> 32:02.144
Super annoying.

32:02.162 --> 32:04.963
- Okay.
Keep telling yourself that.

32:07.334 --> 32:08.984
- I shouldn't have asked you
about him.

32:08.986 --> 32:11.002
That wasn't fair.
- We're married.

32:11.155 --> 32:13.822
You can ask me anything.

32:13.840 --> 32:15.432
- Are you happy?

32:23.000 --> 32:25.275
- I don't love Josh.

32:25.427 --> 32:28.170
But seeing him again,
it just--it reminded me

32:28.172 --> 32:31.264
of who I used to be
before we got married.

32:31.283 --> 32:35.953
The version of myself that was
happy, optimistic, and free.

32:36.104 --> 32:39.623
I don't miss him. I miss me.

32:40.125 --> 32:42.017
- I didn't realize
I made you give that up.

32:42.019 --> 32:45.020
- It's not you.
It's just--it's all of it.

32:45.038 --> 32:48.039
It's this whole life
we built together.

32:49.359 --> 32:52.544
- The day we got married,
I made those vows to you.

32:52.696 --> 32:56.198
I promised I would be
a good partner.

32:56.200 --> 32:59.459
I haven't been.
- Of course you have.

32:59.478 --> 33:02.128
- I didn't even know your dream
was to open a restaurant.

33:02.206 --> 33:05.148
When we get back home,
I am going to do better.

33:05.300 --> 33:07.300
Let me try
and fix this, please.

33:07.319 --> 33:09.044
You've supported me
for all these years.

33:09.046 --> 33:12.805
Now...it's my turn to do
the same for you.

33:12.825 --> 33:15.308
- Okay.

33:15.385 --> 33:17.068
- Do you want to stay here
for a little while

33:17.145 --> 33:19.454
before we have to go back?

33:28.749 --> 33:32.509
- My company isn't the only
thing going under, is it?

33:32.586 --> 33:35.161
When we get home,
we should probably talk about--

33:35.239 --> 33:38.348
- Separating?

33:38.425 --> 33:40.242
I think so too.

33:41.261 --> 33:44.396
- Can we sit here for a while
before we have to go back?

33:46.433 --> 33:47.524
- Yeah.

33:47.601 --> 33:48.933
Let's do that.

33:49.086 --> 33:51.936
<i> [somber music]</i>

33:52.013 --> 33:53.605
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:53.757 --> 33:55.490
[sniffles]

33:59.988 --> 34:03.265
- Are you any closer
to an answer?

34:03.283 --> 34:05.450
- No.

34:05.527 --> 34:09.454
The more I learn, the more
complicated each option gets.

34:09.531 --> 34:12.031
Please, join me.

34:12.051 --> 34:16.053
- Well, life is funny that way.
Ha.

34:16.129 --> 34:18.037
- Have you ever been
at a crossroads?

34:18.115 --> 34:22.801
- Ha. Oh, yes.
A very similar one.

34:22.953 --> 34:25.103
Before Mel,
there was someone else.

34:26.957 --> 34:28.957
Meredith.

34:28.975 --> 34:30.883
- Meredith?
- [laughs]

34:30.961 --> 34:32.903
- Tell me more.

34:32.979 --> 34:38.057
- Oh, well,
she was just magnificent.

34:38.151 --> 34:39.576
But, um...

34:39.727 --> 34:43.229
being with her would have meant
an entirely different life.

34:43.248 --> 34:45.640
And mind you,
this was 50 years ago.

34:45.642 --> 34:49.461
- But if you could go back,
would you pick differently?

34:50.664 --> 34:52.831
- Not a chance.

34:52.983 --> 34:55.592
And he gave me my children.

34:55.819 --> 35:00.388
And without them,
my life would be incomplete.

35:04.494 --> 35:07.753
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:07.831 --> 35:10.774
[both grunt and pant]

35:10.925 --> 35:12.500
- Food.

35:12.519 --> 35:14.152
- Yeah.

35:17.098 --> 35:19.449
Here you go.
- Yes.

35:19.559 --> 35:22.435
Yes, yes, yes.

35:22.454 --> 35:24.696
- Mmm.

35:24.698 --> 35:27.332
Cake.

35:29.035 --> 35:30.869
- Forks?

35:31.021 --> 35:33.296
- Nah. No forks.

35:35.525 --> 35:38.051
Mmm.
Mmm.

35:41.456 --> 35:43.031
- Mmm.

35:43.033 --> 35:45.958
<i> [Latin guitar music]</i>

35:45.978 --> 35:48.812
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:48.963 --> 35:50.872
I'm sorry.

35:50.891 --> 35:58.029
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:03.662 --> 36:07.405
<i> [somber music]</i>

36:07.557 --> 36:13.670
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:13.821 --> 36:17.674
- Hey, hey, it's okay.

36:17.825 --> 36:20.010
- [sniffles]

36:20.161 --> 36:23.829
I never thought
we'd end up like this.

36:23.907 --> 36:26.908
- It's not your fault, Nish.

36:26.927 --> 36:28.852
You knew what you wanted
when we met.

36:29.003 --> 36:33.565
Instead of listening...
I proposed.

36:35.694 --> 36:37.861
- We tried our best.
[sniffles]

36:38.012 --> 36:39.587
And it wasn't good enough.

36:39.589 --> 36:43.091
- Maybe now we can stop
trying to be people we're not

36:43.184 --> 36:45.685
and go back to being friends.

36:45.762 --> 36:48.930
[doorbell rings]

36:48.949 --> 36:52.083
- It's the movers.

36:57.198 --> 36:59.031
- Mom, where's my red shoes?

36:59.109 --> 37:01.459
- Wear the black ones.
- Mom?

37:01.611 --> 37:02.944
- I'm sorry.

37:02.946 --> 37:04.054
- Ms. Desai,

37:04.130 --> 37:06.556
I'm afraid I have
some bad news.

37:06.708 --> 37:09.226
Your husband was running
across the street.

37:09.302 --> 37:12.287
A truck took a wide turn.

37:12.289 --> 37:14.880
I'm sorry,
but he didn't make it.

37:14.958 --> 37:17.883
<i> [ambient music]</i>

37:17.885 --> 37:24.491
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:32.158 --> 37:34.400
- Hey, I need to get back
to the resort,

37:34.478 --> 37:36.160
and you should get dressed
and get the plane ready.

37:36.313 --> 37:39.664
Nisha should be
about ready to go.

37:39.816 --> 37:42.834
- Don't you think we should
talk about this?

37:42.910 --> 37:46.321
- Um...

37:46.323 --> 37:47.672
Javier,

37:47.824 --> 37:49.674
it was a lovely fantasy.

37:49.826 --> 37:52.160
A lovely fantasy.
- Oh...

37:52.162 --> 37:56.523
- But the thing about fantasies
is they...they end.

37:59.669 --> 38:01.278
Come here.

38:16.611 --> 38:18.870
Hey.
- Oh, wow.

38:18.964 --> 38:21.947
You look refreshed.
You sleep well?

38:21.967 --> 38:25.043
- Oh, look, here's Nisha.
- Oh, okay.

38:25.119 --> 38:27.529
- Did you reach a verdict?

38:27.547 --> 38:29.714
- I have.

38:29.791 --> 38:31.641
Me.

38:31.793 --> 38:33.476
I'm the one I should pick.

38:33.553 --> 38:38.039
- Oh. So you're--you're not
going to marry either of them?

38:38.041 --> 38:40.224
- I wanted to know
which version of myself

38:40.377 --> 38:41.467
would be better,

38:41.486 --> 38:45.563
but with both Savin and Josh,
I lost myself.

38:45.715 --> 38:48.974
I love them both,
but in different ways.

38:49.052 --> 38:50.643
And in the end,

38:50.720 --> 38:54.238
getting a divorce from Josh
was...a relief.

38:54.315 --> 38:59.077
And Savin, losing him
was heartbreaking,

38:59.153 --> 39:01.004
just awful.

39:01.155 --> 39:04.065
But if I'm being honest
with myself,

39:04.067 --> 39:06.009
maybe after the grief faded,

39:06.086 --> 39:08.419
I'd feel a little bit
of relief as well,

39:08.496 --> 39:11.514
just to be able
to take charge of my own fate.

39:11.591 --> 39:15.593
So I am making
the last thing on my list

39:15.670 --> 39:19.080
the first thing.

39:19.099 --> 39:21.191
I am going to culinary school.

39:21.267 --> 39:24.694
- Oh!
- Now, not when I'm 60.

39:24.696 --> 39:27.680
- [chuckles]

39:27.757 --> 39:29.348
- I'm done with this list.

39:29.426 --> 39:30.608
- Hmm!

39:30.760 --> 39:32.852
I am happy for you.

39:32.929 --> 39:35.330
- Try one.

39:37.601 --> 39:40.377
<i> [warm music]</i>

39:40.528 --> 39:43.938
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:43.940 --> 39:45.940
- You added cinnamon.
- I did.

39:45.959 --> 39:47.775
And I left them in
two more minutes.

39:47.777 --> 39:49.944
Now they're perfect.
- Mm-hmm.

39:49.963 --> 39:52.797
- Thank you both
for everything.

39:52.874 --> 39:55.950
I didn't know choosing myself
was an option until this.

39:55.952 --> 39:57.969
- I'm just so glad
that you got the answer

39:58.121 --> 39:59.637
you were looking for.

39:59.789 --> 40:01.398
Ruby, I have a few things
that I have to do.

40:01.474 --> 40:04.383
Do you mind taking Nisha
down to the plane, please?

40:04.403 --> 40:05.384
- To Javier?

40:05.404 --> 40:06.644
- To the plane,

40:06.796 --> 40:10.723
which incidentally
is operated by Javier. Yes.

40:10.800 --> 40:14.411
- Okay, sure. All right.

40:14.487 --> 40:15.653
- Great. Okay.

40:15.730 --> 40:17.639
- Please.

40:17.657 --> 40:18.898
- Enjoy.
- [chuckles]

40:18.917 --> 40:20.900
- Bye-bye.

40:20.977 --> 40:23.903
<i> [mellow music]</i>

40:23.980 --> 40:31.136
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:33.156 --> 40:35.173
- You really helped me.

40:35.325 --> 40:40.252
- Well, I hope you get
everything you want

40:40.330 --> 40:43.848
in whatever order you want it.
[both chuckle]

40:44.000 --> 40:48.027
- And I hope you find
another Meredith.

40:56.288 --> 40:59.847
<i> [mellow instrumentals</i>
<i> and singing]</i>

40:59.866 --> 41:07.130
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
